.TH "ib_umem_find_best_pgsz" 9 "ib_umem_find_best_pgsz" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ib_umem_find_best_pgsz \- Find best HW page size to use for this MR
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned long" ib_umem_find_best_pgsz
.BI "(struct ib_umem *umem "  ","
.BI "unsigned long pgsz_bitmap "  ","
.BI "unsigned long virt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "umem" 12
umem struct
.IP "pgsz_bitmap" 12
bitmap of HW supported page sizes
.IP "virt" 12
IOVA
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This helper is intended for HW that support multiple page
sizes but can do only a single page size in an MR.

Returns 0 if the umem requires page sizes not supported by
the driver to be mapped. Drivers always supporting PAGE_SIZE
or smaller will never see a 0 result.
